1. Set up the database params in settings.py
2. Run "python manage.py syncdb" from within OpenILS/admin/ils_admin directory.  
    This will install the necessary Django tables in the database.

see http://www.djangoproject.com/documentation/ for more.

3. If you use Apache2/mod_python, create a symlink to "media" in your document root (e.g /openils/var/web) to the admin media dir:
e.g. /usr/lib/python2.4/site-packages/django/contrib/admin/media/
This can also be accomplished with an Alias directive in Apache config


